Advertainment is a marketing activity that uses media channels or products typically classified as entertainment for distribution. The key distinction attributed to “advertainment” as opposed to “entertaining advertising” is that the advertising is designed to solicit or promote interaction with the campaign. 

Source: http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Transwiki:Advertainment

Although advertainment is frequently used to describe areas where advertising is “placed” into traditional entertainment in an unconventional method such as product placement or a static advertising message in a console game, it is important to clarify that advertainment refers to a form of entertainment, not a method of advertising.  

